eply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.godwinclients.com/sd/haemish_new.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> New Sponsored Trade Skill Treasury Policy</span><hr size=1> Dual Account rules of use<br>
<br>
Each month, we'll have 2 Treasury Hunting Nights. When all monies are collected from each hunt (i.e. 2 times per month), 1/3 (33%) of that money will be set aside in a special account for trade skill funding. No more than 1/3rd shall be set aside, and none of the 1/3rd set aside shall be considered available for the regular guild treasury (which will be used to buy siege engines, guild housing, and any other things to be purchased for the guild).  The guild income will be split directly into two separately tracked accounts (see the guild treasury web page). 1/3 will go into the Trade Skill Account and 2/3 will go into the General Fund.<br>
<br>
The purpose of the Trade Skill Account is to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  supplement</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the large sum of gold necessary to raise trade skills.  The primary source of gold to advance one's trade skill will come from the trades person themselves.<br>
<br>
The sponsored trade skill people may change the method used to access the Trade Skill Account so long as they are in agreement with the method (i.e. they could all split it up evenly, or more could go to one person) on a bi-weekly basis.  No matter what method used, it will be published in the Trade Skill forum.  The sponsored trades persons receiving funds and the sum of those funds will also be publically recorded.<br>
<br>
By receiving <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  any</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> supplemental funding from the Trade Skill Account, the sponsored tradesfolk agree to use this supplemental money to advance their trade skill between the time they are given the money and the next Treasury Hunting night <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  and</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to report their skill gain regularly in the Trade Skill thread (and also posted on the Trade Contact web page).  As guild-sponsored tradesfolk, they can not charge more than material cost for making items for guild members or alternates.<br>
<br>
As only 33% of the Dagger Night proceeds are placed in the Trade Skill Account the sponsored tradesfolk must use account wisely. This fund will only <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  very slightly</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> offset the overall costs of skill advancement for those taking on trade skills for the guild and every little bit helps.  More importantly, these monies represent the work of them and their guildmates.<br>
<br>
A limited transactional history will be kept in the Treasury forum (only a few months worth to keep the size of the thread down).  The status of both the General Fund and the Trade Skill Account will be tracked on the Treasury web page.<br>
<br>
------------<br>
Some members have generously made direct Donations to the guild.  Since this isn't per-se income, members donating to the guild may specify if the donation should go 100% into the General Fund, 100% into the Trade Skill Account, or considered as &quot;guild income&quot; and split as described above.  Members wishing to donate to advance a <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>specific</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> trade skill may specify that or just donate to that sponsored trades person directly.<br>
------------<br>
